<h1>{$node_name}</h1>

<p>The Module Remote SMTP allow to add a SMTP Server generally used to send messages from a mail client to a mail server.</p>
<p>The fields to configure a Remote SMTP Server are:</p>
<ul>
    <li><b>Status: </b> Status of connection SMTP Server.</li>
    <li><b>SMTP Server: </b> Common emails servers used.</li>
    <li><b>Domain: </b> Domain of SMTP Server.</li>
    <li><b>Port: </b> Port to establish connection with SMTP Server.</li>
    <li><b>User: </b>Username of email account from SMTP Server.</li>
    <li><b>Password: </b>Password of email account from SMTP Server</li>
    <li><b>TLS Enable: </b>To enable certificates of TLS(Transport Layer Security). Some SMTP server like Gmail requires this certificates.</li>
</ul>
